      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "Muslim Aid America demonstrates a high level of operational leaness, as evidenced by its <cite id=\"7\">93.2% program expense ratio</cite>, which exceeds the <cite id=\"8\">peer median of 83.0%</cite>. This financial discipline allows the organization to maximize the impact of every dollar. Furthermore, the charity has shown robust growth with a <cite id=\"9\">3-year revenue CAGR of 24.2%</cite>, indicating increasing donor trust and expanded capacity to respond to international emergencies. Their commitment to transparency is reflected in their <cite id=\"10\">Platinum Seal of Transparency from Candid</cite>, the highest level of recognition for nonprofit disclosure."
      ],
      "summary": "Muslim Aid America operates as a major humanitarian relief organization dedicated to assisting victims of natural disasters, conflict, and extreme poverty. The organization reported <cite id=\"1\">$26,177,076 in total revenue</cite> for the 2023 fiscal year, demonstrating a significant capacity to mobilize resources for global crises. Their operations are characterized by an extremely high <cite id=\"2\">program expense ratio of 93.2%</cite>, which indicates that nearly all donor funds are directed toward direct aid rather than administrative overhead. This efficiency is further highlighted by their fundraising model, which costs only <cite id=\"3\">$0.04 to raise every $1</cite>. The charity maintains a broad geographic reach, serving vulnerable populations across <cite id=\"4\">the Middle East, Asia, and Africa</cite>. By focusing on essential needs such as <cite id=\"5\">food security, water, and healthcare</cite>, the organization addresses the most urgent drivers of human suffering. As a faith-based entity, it provides a structured platform for <cite id=\"6\">verified zakat-eligible giving</cite>, ensuring that religious obligations are fulfilled through impactful humanitarian projects.",
